26 THIS TITLE; AND
27 (III) MAY DIRECT PRODUCTION OF ESTIMATES OF REVENUES
28 AND EXPENDITURES COMPILED BY THE STATE BOARD OF REVENUE ESTIMATES,
29 THE BUREAU OF REVENUE ESTIMATES, OR THE CONSENSUS REVENUE
30 MONITORING AND FORECASTING GROUP.
31 (2) (I) THE OPINIONS AND GUIDANCE ISSUED BY THE NEUTRAL
32 ARBITRATOR UNDER THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE ADVISORY ON THE PARTIES AND
33 THE GOVERNOR.

10 HOUSE BILL 604
1 (II) THE USE OF A NEUTRAL ARBITRATOR DOES NOT DIMINISH
2 OR LIMIT THE RIGHTS OF ANY PARTY TO FILE AND PURSUE A COMPLAINT OF UNFAIR
3 LABOR PRACTICES BEFORE THE BOARD.
4 (B) (C) (1) IF EITHER PARTY DECLARES AN IMPASSE ON OR AFTER
5 OCTOBER 1, ARBITRATION SHALL PROCEED AS DESCRIBED IN THIS SUBSECTION.
6 (2) (I) ON THE FIFTH BUSINESS DAY AFTER THE IMPASSE IS
7 DECLARED, EACH PARTY SHALL SUBMIT TO THE NEUTRAL ARBITRATOR, IN WRITING
8 AND WITH A COPY TO THE OTHER PARTY, A LAST, BEST, AND FINAL OFFER,
9 INCLUDING:
10 1. ALL PROVISIONS IN THE EXISTING MEMORANDUM OF
11 UNDERSTANDING NOT TO BE MODIFIED;
12 2. ALL NEW, AMENDED, OR MODIFIED MEMORANDUM OF
13 UNDERSTANDING PROVISIONS AGREED TO BY THE PARTIES BEFORE THE IMPASSE
14 WAS DECLARED THAT ARE TO BE INCLUDED THROUGH WRITTEN MUTUAL
15 AGREEMENT; AND
16 3. SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS
17 PARAGRAPH, DETAILED FURTHER PROVISIONS THAT A PARTY IS PROPOSING FOR
18 INCLUSION IN A MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING.
19 (II) FURTHER PROVISIONS ARE LIMITED TO SPECIFIC
20 PROPOSALS THAT WERE SUBMITTED IN WRITING TO THE OTHER PARTY AND WERE
21 THE SUBJECT OF COLLECTIVE BARGAINING BETWEEN THE PARTIES UP TO THE TIME
22 OF IMPASSE, INCLUDING PROPOSALS THAT THE PARTIES HAVE DECIDED TO
23 INCLUDE IN THE MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING THROUGH WRITTEN MUTUAL
24 AGREEMENT.
25 (3) THE NEUTRAL ARBITRATOR ACTING AS A MEDIATOR SHALL
26 ATTEMPT TO RESOLVE THE IMPASSE BEFORE A FORMAL HEARING ON THE IMPASSE.
27 (4) (I) WITHIN 30 CALENDAR DAYS AFTER A DECLARED IMPASSE,
28 THE NEUTRAL ARBITRATOR SHALL HOLD A FORMAL HEARING AT WHICH THE
29 PARTIES MAY SUBMIT, IN WRITING OR ORAL TESTIMONY, ALL INFORMATION OR
30 DATA SUPPORTING THE FINAL POSITIONS.
31 (II) ABSENT MUTUAL AGREEMENT BETWEEN THE PARTIES, OR
32 AS OTHERWISE ORDERED BY THE NEUTRAL ARBITRATOR, THE FORMAL HEARING
33 SHALL CONCLUDE WITHIN 45 CALENDAR DAYS AFTER THE IMPASSE DATE.

